cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the transmission of status update packets in real-time applications, which is a key aspect of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper introduces a novel metric, Age-of-Information (AoI), which measures the freshness of information in status update scenarios. This is related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper considers a two-node tandem queuing model for the two computing schemes, which can be seen as a control system. 
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses the use of mobile edge computing (MEC) to reduce age for computation-intensive messages, which is related to distributed and parallel computing. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper considers two computing models: local computing by user itself and remote computing at MEC server, which can be seen as two agents in a multiagent system.
